    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-02-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-28T17:35:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[Responsibility in Federal Contracts Act - Prohibits the Federal Government from contracting with companies that have failed to certify the most recent periodic financial report required under the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002 that is due before the contract award date.<p>States the period of prohibition shall remain in effect for one year beginning on the date that the most recent periodic report was due.<p>Requires the Securities and Exchange Commission to make available to the public on a quarterly basis a list of companies that have failed to make such certification.]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Responsibility in Federal Contracts Act</title>
